WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.365
Roles in the Dental Healthcare Team

00:00:02.365 --> 00:00:04.023
Clinical Roles:

00:00:04.023 --> 00:00:04.558
Dentist:

00:00:04.558 --> 00:00:11.614
Diagnoses and treats oral diseases, creates treatment plans, and oversees the dental team to ensure coordinated care.

00:00:11.614 --> 00:00:13.120
Dental Hygienist:

00:00:13.950 --> 00:00:21.831
Focuses on preventive care, including cleanings and fluoride treatments, while educating patients about effective oral hygiene practices.

00:00:21.831 --> 00:00:23.108
Dental Assistant:

00:00:23.938 --> 00:00:31.612
Supports the dentist during procedures, manages infection control, ensures patient comfort, and prepares dental materials.

00:00:31.612 --> 00:00:32.937
Lab Technician:

00:00:33.767 --> 00:00:41.856
Creates custom dental prosthetics, such as crowns, bridges, and dentures, ensuring that they fit properly and meet patient needs.

00:00:41.856 --> 00:00:43.637
Administrative Roles:

00:00:43.637 --> 00:00:44.834
Receptionist:

00:00:45.664 --> 00:00:52.997
Manages appointments, patient inquiries, and maintains patient records, serving as the first point of contact for visitors.

00:00:52.997 --> 00:00:54.226
Office Manager:

00:00:55.056 --> 00:01:03.304
Oversees daily operations of the dental practice, manages staff, ensures regulatory compliance, and enhances office efficiency.

00:01:03.304 --> 00:01:04.831
Treatment Coordinator:

00:01:05.661 --> 00:01:12.876
Assists patients in understanding treatment options and financial commitments, while coordinating scheduling and addressing patient concerns.
